HB 1167 Engrossed 2026 Regular Session Glorioso
Designates the elevated portion of La. Hwy. 433 from Dubee Pena Rd. to Rivet Dr. in
Slidell, La. as the "Emile 'Uncle Tobe' Galatas Memorial Bridge".
Designates a portion of U.S. Hwy. 11 from the Dr. T.J. Smith, Sr. Expressway to La. Hwy.
41 in Pearl River, La. as the "Captain Steven Gaudet, Jr. Memorial Highway".
Directs the Dept. of Transportation and Development (DOTD) to erect and maintain
appropriate signage reflecting these designations provided local or private monies are
received by the DOTD equal to its actual costs for material, fabrication, mounting posts, and
installation of the signage, not to exceed the sum of $750 per sign for the "Emile 'Uncle
Tobe' Galatas Memorial Bridge" and $2,250 per sign for the "Captain Steven Gaudet, Jr.
Memorial Highway".
Summary of Amendments Adopted by House
The Committee Amendments Proposed by House Committee on Transportation,
Highways and Public Works to the original bill:
1. Add "Memorial" to the "Emile 'Uncle Tobe' Galatas Bridge" designation.
